This paper discusses a blockchain-based service for proving the provenance of online digital identity, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also mentions the use of deep learning for DP analytics and visualization, which could be categorized under cybernetics (cs.CY) or social and information networks (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the storage and management of data, which could be categorized under databases (cs.DB) or systems and control (cs.SD).
